Its Germany vs Spain | Beijing 2008 | Sports | The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata)
                                                                                                                                                                                                             Its Germany vs Spain
                      
	Beijing: World Cup champions Germany and Spain go into Saturdays Olympic mens field hockey final with Germany contesting their first final since winning the gold medal at Barcelona in 1992 and Spain bidding for their first Olympic title after losing the deciders in 1980 and 1996.         
	Spain, widely regarded as the best mens team not to have won the Olympic gold, will be wary of the Germans who beat them 1-0 in the preliminary league.         
	On Thursday, Spain fought back after being two goals down to upset defending champions Australia 3-2 in a thrilling semi-final.         
	Germany beat the Netherlands 4-3 in the penalty shoot-out after the European heavyweights were locked 1-1 at the end of extra-time.           (AFP)                                                                                                                      
